  10. We also recommended that the designated Property Officer:


     a. Maintain Property Cards for all properties of the Municipality;
     b. Provide Property Tags for each equipment with complete labels;
     c. Update PAR of each employee every three years;
     d. Provide adequate storage for Unserviceable Equipment; and
     e. Request for disposal of unserviceable properties.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant agreed to:

     a. Verify previous years’ accounting records  on  fund  transfers  to
        confirm Liquidations Reports submitted to DA in previous years  on
        Trading  Post,  otherwise,  gather  all  necessary  documents  for
        submission to DA;
     b. Submit Liquidation Reports on Bagsakan Project;
     c. Deposit to the Bureau of Treasury the unused fund transferred from
        DA for the  Bagsakan Project amounting to P178,374.86;
     d. Trace the fund source used of the excess amount used  to  pay  for
        Vermi Production project of DA in excess of the fund transfers, to
        avoid disallowance in audit;
     e. Submit Liquidation Reports on a  monthly  basis,  in  coordination
        with MAO, on all funds transferred to the Municipality;
     f. Maintain a separate subsidiary ledger  for  every  project/program
        and record each fund transfer in a single project/program SL.

