We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
Inventory Team to prepare and submit a revised RPCPPE in the prescribed format and indicate all the required information pertaining to the properties being accounted, duly signed by the Inventory Committee and approved by the LCE;
Propery Officer-Designate to maintain Property Cards for each kind of PPE owned by the LGU and periodically reconcile the same with the Accountant’s records;
Municipal Accountant provide the complete data in the prescribed PPELC, update and reconcile the same with the records of the Property Officer.
The LGU officials concerned assured the Audit Team that depreciation of all PPEs will be taken up in CY 2018 when the PPEs will be transferred to the General Fund. Management committed to abide with the recommendations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive provide the necessary assistance to the Municipal Treasurer, in terms of manpower, in order to intensify and maximize collection of Real Property/Special Education Taxes.
We also recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Treasurer to:
1. design a strategy to enhance extensive and effective Tax Collection Campaign program;
2. 	send notices of delinquency to each concerned property owner;
3. post a complete list of delinquent property owners at the main entrance of the Municipal Hall and in such other publicly accessible and conspicuous places in each Barangay of the LGU;
4. prepare a certified complete list of all real property tax delinquencies which remained uncollected or unpaid for at least one (1) year, stating the reason or reasons for such non-collection or non-payment;
5. submit the list to the Sanggunian Bayan on or before December 31 of the year immediately succeeding the year in which the delinquencies were incurred, with a request for assistance in the enforcement of the remedies for collection either by administrative action thru levy on real property or by judicial action.
Management thru its LCE welcomed the recommendation and committed to implement the same within the year.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the MDRRM Council, through the MDRRM Officer, to include in a separate caption in the MDRRMF Investment Plan, the list of projects and activities that will be paid out of the LDRRMF Trust Fund.
To ensure accuracy in their reports and for purposes of check and balance, we recommended that the MDRRMO, the Municipal Budget Officer and the Municipal Accountant:
reconcile monthly their relevant records on LDRRM Fund;
monitor strictly the utilization of the MDRRMF so that the funds appropriated for each PPA are utilized accordingly as planned, and;
submit to the Audit Team an explanation for the discrepancies noted in their reports.
The MDRRMO averred that supplemental LDRRMFIP was actually made. However, none was submitted to COA.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive:
constitute the Local Council for the Protection of Children in the LGU from among its department heads, with himself as the Chairman;
require the created LCPC to prepare the LCPC Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the local development plan, and;
Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that 1% of the IRA of the Municipality is appropriated for the implementation of LCPC-identified programs, projects and activities for child protection and welfare and prevention of juvenile delinquency.
The management assured that they would prepare specific budget for LCPC in CY 2018.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Accountant to:
ensure that the net take home pay of all employees of the Municipality of Kawayan is not below the minimum amount prescribed by law;
verify the paying capacity of an employee before signing loan applications so that the mandated net take home pay of the employee will be complied;
authorize deductions only if the loan was obtained from accredited financing institutions enumerated by law.
Management commits that they will stop granting loans to employees who have net take home pay of P4,000.00 below.  Also, the municipal mayor assured to draft a memo pertaining of the said issue.
